ss="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-djTQOc gLxCly pf-29_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-30_">Why digital governance, leadership, and operational readiness are shaping CQC outcomes - and how your organisation can stay ahead with ComplyPlus™</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a7ab14b1-0ba5-4dcd-b9e1-22b6c6f6fbdc"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In today’s high-pressure regulatory environment, the Care Quality Commission (CQC) is placing growing emphasis on three critical areas: leadership, governance, and digital preparedness. The latest wave of inspection reports makes one thing clear – compliance is no longer just about having the right documents in place. It’s about proving, in real time, that your organisation is safe, effective, and well-led.
<br></span></p><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-3f94f80a-3255-427c-8d7f-7f2f73d9127a"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">At The Mandatory Training Group, we support health and social care providers in translating regulatory expectations into everyday operational practice. As Chief Operations Officer, I’ve worked with hundreds of services across the UK to embed smarter compliance through ComplyPlus™ - our digital platform that supports inspection readiness, evidence-based governance, and workforce training alignment.
<br></span></p><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-38_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-c0df8813-91b9-4778-925b-d70124df0e77"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In this blog, Lewis Normoyle breaks down the key trends from recent CQC reports, what they mean for your service, and how ComplyPlus™ can help you avoid common pitfalls.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-41_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-djTQOc gLxCly pf-42_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-43_">The CQC's evolving focus - From paperwork to proactive leadership</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-45_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-cdb9e122-b6c6-46fb-9c0e-795af474c9e7"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The CQC assesses providers against five key questions:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dISoPS kgxkyr pf-48_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-49_">Is the service safe?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-51_">Is it effective?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-53_">Is it caring?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-55_">Is it responsive?
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-57_">Is it well-led?
</li></ul><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-59_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f5341eb2-7d46-4c37-8802-804cd3612129"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">While all five are important,<em> “well-led”</em> is increasingly the tipping point for inspection outcomes. Why? Because effective leadership underpins everything, from risk mitigation to culture and accountability.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-62_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-186eaafb-3e6b-424e-927b-bb4c0725a402"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In the most recent inspection cycles, services that lacked clear leadership, structured oversight, and a digital trail of compliance were far more likely to be rated <em>“Requires Improvement”</em> or <em>“Inadequate.”</em>
<br>
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-65_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-djTQOc gLxCly pf-66_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-67_">Four common compliance failures found in recent reports
</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-69_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-3511c563-836d-458c-8840-9fdb4b5b5b7f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Across both NHS and independent providers, several recurring weaknesses have emerged:
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-72_">1. Weak governance and oversight
</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-74_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-97dc2178-c8c8-4594-8d8f-7f11334e13f6"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Many services had policies on paper, but no systems to implement, monitor, or review them. This left frontline teams unclear on expectations, and leadership unable to provide inspectors with documented evidence of control.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-77_">2. Poor training compliance
</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-79_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-7f11334e-13f6-439a-9564-f367362742b2"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">A consistent theme was missed statutory and mandatory training updates - sometimes due to staff turnover, but often due to a lack of central oversight. In several cases, providers were unable to produce valid certificates or up-to-date training records during inspections.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-82_">3. Outdated risk assessments
</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-84_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f3673627-42b2-4ae8-bb3d-827da06945cb"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Infection prevention and control, safeguarding, fire safety, and moving and handling were some of the areas where risk assessments were either missing or outdated. Inspectors flagged this as evidence of a compliance system that was reactive rather than live and dynamic.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-87_">4. Inaction on feedback and incidents</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-89_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-827da069-45cb-4c77-b09f-3025c734f512"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">CQC reports repeatedly noted that incidents, complaints, and staff concerns were not being followed up effectively. Where lessons weren’t documented, shared, or used to inform change, services were marked down for lacking a learning culture.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-92_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-djTQOc gLxCly pf-93_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-94_">What do these findings mean for you
</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-96_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-2d81a2ac-5b49-4a73-a025-f3b1dcd70348"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">If your service is still relying on siloed systems, paper-based logs, or last-minute audit scrambles, these reports should serve as a wake-up call.
<br></span></p><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-99_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a90763db-b8be-49ec-b917-c2d13bfff716"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Regulators are looking for:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dISoPS kgxkyr pf-102_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-103_">Ongoing training oversight, not just certificates, during inspection.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-105_">Live evidence of risk management, not historic documentation.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-107_">Leadership involvement in governance, not just delegation.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-109_">Systems that show how lessons are tracked, shared, and acted upon.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-111_">How ComplyPlus™ helps you meet and exceed CQC standards
</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-113_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-68ede960-df36-4332-b224-0aed421d0784"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">At The Mandatory Training Group, we developed ComplyPlus™ to give providers the tools they need to proactively manage compliance and governance - every day, not just before an inspection:
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-116_">Centralised policy and document control</h3><p class="sc-fPrdjK bLmLvT pf-118_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-3518a384-9149-4905-94e9-a92ae47b8dd5"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Upload, assign, and version-control all key documents in one place. Ensure policies are read, acknowledged, and reviewed with full audit trails for regulators.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-121_">Real-time training oversight
